snippet.textDisplay:
How much of a loser must one be to already not be satisfied but the 4G speed ?
5G is waaayy overkill. Who need to download a movie in 5s on their phone, srly ?
The dangers of 5G far outweight any advantage of a global 5G network.
I'm sensitive to phone waves, I can feel them, I'm perpetually sick when I go in some cities, and during by adolescence, I used to live near a cell tower, and was ALWAYS sick, like a common cold symptom minus the runing nose. I was very lethargic, had migranes, and nausea.
I move out to the country side, and I healed in only a day, and never got sick again, until I moved back to the city, and withing the first days, I was back to being sick. Nothing else had changed, not the food, not the sleep, only the environment.
I also get nausea when someone has their phone next to me for too long, with the internet connectin on, or making a call.

It is scientifically proven, over and over again, that water reacts to waves, water is displaced, the H2O molecules spin differently, the hydrogen bonds are modified (the water matrix structes itself differently).
Every cell in our body contains water. It is undeniable that waves have an effect on us.
But we don't notice it because we bathe in them, it has become the norm.
Take anyone from a city, and bring them to the countryside with no phone signal. You wwill see how quickly they feel better, how fast they start shredding weight, how much more energy they have. Because their body finaly can work correctly and calmly (waves stress the body into fight or flight state).
